text: Guy on CNBC says 80% of companies beat estimates and markets will continue to rally. See "Dumb and Dumber" a column I wrote on @TSTRealMoneyPro recently - of course they did realmoneypro.thestreet.com/d…

"That said, I wanted to highlight what I believe to be the single dumbest remark that numerous "talking heads" have utilized in support of a Bullish market view over the last week. That is, the statement that 80% of the company's that have reported 1Q2018 results beat consensus

EPS expectations - up from the more typical 70% average beat over time. Given the introduction of the tax bill, in late December, 2017, which markedly reduced the statutory tax rate -- this has to be the single dumbest remark in support of the markets I have heard in years.

In fact, at least to me, it is surprising that the number of companies beating the consensus EPS estimates currently stand at only 80%. Don't listen to this pablum - expressed with authority - in the business news media and don't be an earnings twit."
.Thx Bil Nice.
